      "line": 4406,
      "term": "energy",
      "snippet": "strong. Think carefully about sealing your dome. If you don’t do it properly at first, you'll end up spending four times as much energy (and money) in getting a watertight seal. Because | was in too much of a hurry in sealing, it rained inside our dome in the first rainstorm. The three of us ended up huddled in a dry spot on the floor in the least wet sleeping bag. Later | remedied the leaks, but the hassle was frightful. Everything"
